WEBVTT

00:20.954 --> 00:22.454
Paul:
Yeah, you want to put it up

00:22.456 --> 00:24.123
A couple of inches
on your side, love.

00:24.125 --> 00:26.025
Okeydokey.

00:27.460 --> 00:29.128
You really think

00:29.130 --> 00:32.631
Anyone's gonna pay to see
this rich nancy sing show tunes?

00:32.633 --> 00:34.299
I wouldn't.

00:34.301 --> 00:36.135
He gives me the creeps.

00:36.137 --> 00:38.137
He keeps wanting
to spoon-feed me,

00:38.139 --> 00:40.806
And then making
these weird airplane noises.

00:40.808 --> 00:43.909
We should just leave,
all of us, join a new show.

00:43.911 --> 00:46.078
Penny, do you really think

00:46.080 --> 00:48.313
If there wasn't another option,
some other freak show out there,

00:48.315 --> 00:49.581
I wouldn't take you away

00:49.583 --> 00:51.417
In an instant?

00:51.419 --> 00:53.085
There's nowhere to go.

00:53.087 --> 00:55.087
Our world is dying,
sweetheart.

00:55.089 --> 00:57.890
This is the end
of the line.

00:59.592 --> 01:01.593
But we've got to eat,

01:01.595 --> 01:04.763
And that kid's got money
pouring out of his ears.

01:04.765 --> 01:06.598
I say we let him
keep feeding us

01:06.600 --> 01:08.333
Until that lemon
runs out of juice.

01:08.335 --> 01:10.436
Dandy:
<i>No, no, no!</i>

01:10.438 --> 01:12.037
Turn it off!

01:12.039 --> 01:13.505
I told you
a million trillion times,

01:13.507 --> 01:14.673
The blue light

01:14.675 --> 01:16.108
Is for "night and day."

01:16.110 --> 01:18.243
Blue symbolizes night.

01:19.379 --> 01:20.846
For "anything goes,"

01:20.848 --> 01:22.681
I need the magenta light

01:22.683 --> 01:25.284
To accentuate
my spirited rendition.

01:25.286 --> 01:26.685
(groans)

01:26.687 --> 01:28.020
I'm surrounded by amateurs.

01:30.356 --> 01:32.291
Ah, flipper boy!

01:32.293 --> 01:34.126
You're back.

01:34.128 --> 01:36.628
Did you hang the banner
in clear view for all to see?

01:36.630 --> 01:38.030
Yes, sir, just as instructed.

01:38.032 --> 01:39.298
Good, good.

01:39.300 --> 01:40.699
How many tickets have we sold?

01:41.801 --> 01:43.802
Um, well,

01:43.804 --> 01:45.904
As of this time, none...

01:45.906 --> 01:48.207
Quite yet.

01:48.209 --> 01:49.908
You haven't sold
a single ticket?

01:49.910 --> 01:51.376
Well, we only put
out the banner

01:51.378 --> 01:53.212
Half an hour ago.

01:53.214 --> 01:55.380
The town hasn't gotten wind
of your new act.

01:55.382 --> 01:58.117
I don't understand.

01:59.552 --> 02:01.386
You must have done
something wrong.

02:01.388 --> 02:02.921
Sir, this is quite
typical.

02:02.923 --> 02:04.389
You haven't got
a lot of experience

02:04.391 --> 02:05.724
In this sort of thing,
but you'll see.

02:05.726 --> 02:08.827
You think you're so smart.

02:08.829 --> 02:11.497
You don't know anything,
you stupid freak.

02:11.499 --> 02:12.831
He's only trying to help.

02:12.833 --> 02:15.968
Oh, shut up, you ugly cow.

02:15.970 --> 02:17.503
