Please just let
me out of here,

26:26.619 --> 26:29.453
And let's go home.

26:29.455 --> 26:30.688
Please.

26:30.690 --> 26:32.957
I want to go home.

26:32.959 --> 26:34.625
Dot:
Well, you're about
to go home.

26:34.627 --> 26:37.962
Right down to hell.

26:37.964 --> 26:42.866
Bette, you of all people
know my heart.

26:50.308 --> 26:52.443
I hate you.

26:53.545 --> 26:54.778
I hate you!

26:56.715 --> 26:59.316
For taking my friends
from me!

26:59.318 --> 27:03.654
I felt so blessed
to finally have friends.

27:03.656 --> 27:06.056
And you took them all.

27:06.058 --> 27:09.994
Desiree: A lot of freaks
died on these cursed grounds.

27:09.996 --> 27:12.162
Some by your hand and some not.

27:12.164 --> 27:14.164
A man came
through here

27:14.166 --> 27:17.501
And started putting our kind
in glass jars.

27:17.503 --> 27:20.504
Filled up a museum
with our kind.

27:20.506 --> 27:23.340
Saw it with
my own eyes!

27:23.342 --> 27:25.909
That's where you think
freaks belong--

27:25.911 --> 27:30.614
Powerless, behind glass,
a human car crash

27:30.616 --> 27:35.452
To stare at and remind
you how lucky you are.

27:35.454 --> 27:36.453
(knob creaks)

27:36.455 --> 27:38.288
Well, maybe that's true.

27:38.290 --> 27:42.026
Maybe that's all we are, but let
me tell you this, pretty boy.

27:42.028 --> 27:46.697
You may look like a
motion picture dreamboat,

27:46.699 --> 27:50.601
But you are the biggest freak
of them all.

27:53.038 --> 27:54.938
(knob creaks)

27:57.375 --> 27:59.443
(yelling)

28:02.781 --> 28:03.781
(grunts)

28:03.783 --> 28:06.617
Please! I'll give you money.

28:06.619 --> 28:09.119
I have so much money.

28:09.121 --> 28:11.288
Assholes like you think
you can get away with anything.

28:11.290 --> 28:12.289
But I can't die!

28:12.291 --> 28:15.292
You see, I'm immortal!

28:15.294 --> 28:17.961
You are going to die!

28:17.963 --> 28:20.297
We sentence you and your
whole rotten world to death.

28:20.299 --> 28:21.298
Look at us.

28:21.300 --> 28:22.900
We will always win,

28:22.902 --> 28:24.735
Because we'll always defend
each other to the death.

28:24.737 --> 28:27.304
You want to know why? Because
we have no one else to turn to.

28:28.406 --> 28:30.974
The freaks shall inherit
the earth.

28:44.923 --> 28:47.257
(yells)

28:47.259 --> 28:48.759
(grunting)

28:48.761 --> 28:51.328
(yelling)

28:53.765 --> 28:56.166
(yelling continues)

29:01.773 --> 29:03.841
Please!

29:05.443 --> 29:07.678
Please!

29:07.680 --> 29:10.681
(sobbing)

29:14.853 --> 29:16.286
I hate you!

29:16.288 --> 29:19.690
I hate you! I hate you!
I hate you! I hate you!

29:27.132 --> 29:28.799
(chuckles)

29:28.801 --> 29:31.034
(gasping)

29:37.041 --> 29:38.542
(muffled yelling)

29:52.824 --> 29:55.626
Heck of a show.

29:57.662 --> 29:59.663
That boy

29:59.665 --> 30:02.733
Is a star.

30:16.080 --> 30:18.782
(movie projector clicking,
fanfare playing)

30:18.784 --> 30:20.284
Announcer: <i>Every little girl</i>
<i>dreams of becoming</i>

30:20.286 --> 30:22.119
<i>A hollywood star,</i>
<i>and now thanks to</i>

30:22.121 --> 30:24.421
<i>The hollywood chamber of</i>
<i>commerce, the ones that make it</i>

30:24.423 --> 30:26.089
<i>To the top will have</i>
<i>their names etched</i>

30:26.091 --> 30:28.192
<i>Into the very streets</i>
<i>of this magical town.</i>

30:28.194 --> 30:30.260
<i>Welcome to the newly created</i>
<i>hollywood walk of fame</i>

30:30.262 --> 30:32.362
<i>In los angeles, california.</i>

30:32.364 --> 30:34.431
<i>Today, we're honoring</i>
<i>the queen of Friday night,</i>

30:34.433 --> 30:37.868
<i>Miss elsa mars--</i>
<i>winner of three emmy awards</i>

30:37.870 --> 30:40.437
<i>For her groundbreaking variety</i>
<i>show</i> the elsa mars hour,

30:40.439 --> 30:42.873
<i>A program which has</i>
<i>bravely expanded the notion</i>

30:42.875 --> 30:44.775
<i>Of what television can be.</i>

30:44.777 --> 30:46.777
<i>And we mustn't forget</i>
<i>she's a recording star</i>

30:46.779 --> 30:49.780
<i>With three gold albums</i>
<i>honoring her german heritage:</i>

30:49.782 --> 30:53.116
Ich bin elsa mars,
du bist mein baby,

30:53.118 --> 30:56.954
<i>And her holiday favorite,</i>
<i>merry christmas, knuddelmaus.</i>

30:56.956 --> 30:58.789
<i>Of course, no woman's life</i>
<i>would be complete</i>

30:58.791 --> 31:00.624
<i>Without a wonderful man</i>
<i>by her side:</i>

31:00.626 --> 31:02.292
<i>Her husband and longtime</i>
<i>manager michael beck,</i>

31:02.294 --> 31:03.961
<i>Whom she married</i>
<i>in a private ceremony</i>

31:03.963 --> 31:06.463
<i>At her palatial home</i>
<i>in beverly hills.</i>

31:06.465 --> 31:08.398
<i>There are elsa's</i>
<i>beloved spaniels,</i>

31:08.400 --> 31:11.568
<i>Showbiz and box office--</i>
<i>a gift from michael.</i>

31:11.570 --> 31:14.905
<i>With all her many honors,</i>
<i>elsa mars can now add a star,</i>

31:14.907 --> 31:17.341
<i>On the hollywood walk of fame.</i>

31:17.343 --> 31:19.476
(fanfare ends)

31:19.478 --> 31:23.413
I adore being the star
of   <i>the elsa mars hour.</i>

31:23.415 --> 31:26.583
I mean, who wouldn't love
having their own tv show,

31:26.585 --> 31:29.086
Surrounded by such talent?

31:29.088 --> 31:33.824
Especially my own
real-life cowboy

31:33.826 --> 31:36.660
And personal manager,

31:36.662 --> 31:39.930
Michael "mr. Hollywood" beck.

31:39.932 --> 31:43.934
But being a television star
is a lot of hard work.

31:43.936 --> 31:46.336
So is wrangling that star.
(chuckles)

31:46.338 --> 31:51.909
And that's why we drink
campfire gold instant coffee.

31:51.911 --> 31:54.511
Mmm.

31:54.513 --> 31:56.780
Because...

31:56.782 --> 32:00.350
Herding cattle
isn't the only hard work...

32:02.453 --> 32:03.620
Cut!

32:03.622 --> 32:05.789
(bell rings)

32:05.791 --> 32:08.525
This is shite! This is shite!

32:08.527 --> 32:09.860
Pure shite!

32:09.862 --> 32:11.295
Where are the
writers? Huh?

32:11.297 --> 32:13.130
The writers! Are you hiding?

32:13.132 --> 32:14.798
I shouldn't blame you...

32:14.800 --> 32:16.300
Michael: Darling,
it's a coffee commercial.

32:16.302 --> 32:18.201
Just say the damn words
and move on?

32:18.203 --> 32:19.870
First of all,
this coffee tastes

32:19.872 --> 32:21.038
Like piss.

32:21.040 --> 32:22.973
But why would you
paint me

32:22.975 --> 32:25.142
As some dumb,
headstrong animal

32:25.144 --> 32:26.910
That my husband
has to wrangle?

32:26.912 --> 32:28.078
Huh?

32:28.080 --> 32:29.546
I mean, where
is the charm?

32:29.548 --> 32:31.715
Now, go work on it
for a while!

32:31.717 --> 32:33.784
I'll be in my dressing room.

32:36.321 --> 32:39.323
<i>Scheisse!</i>

32:39.325 --> 32:41.725
(door opens)
michael:
Knock knock, darling.

32:41.727 --> 32:43.493
There's someone to see you.

32:43.495 --> 32:47.998
Naughty you, demeaning your
wife in front of the world.

32:48.000 --> 32:49.666
Was that amusing
for you?

32:49.668 --> 32:51.335
We're working hard
to try and find

32:51.337 --> 32:52.669
Something
that'll please you.

32:52.671 --> 32:54.838
In the meantime,
remember judy manners?

32:54.840 --> 32:56.506
Vp of publicity
for the network?

32:56.508 --> 32:59.242
She wants to discuss promotion
for the Halloween show.

32:59.244 --> 33:00.911
You're joking, aren't you?

33:00.913 --> 33:03.580
We'd like to do a spread
for <i>parade magazine--</i>

33:03.582 --> 33:05.248
You two at home,

33:05.250 --> 33:07.117
Carving pumpkins,

33:07.119 --> 33:09.586
Maybe baking some
pfeffernusse cookies

33:09.588 --> 33:12.823
For the trick-or-treaters.

33:14.759 --> 33:17.427
What my pussy of a husband

33:17.429 --> 33:20.197
Has neglected to tell you

33:20.199 --> 33:22.766
Is there will be
no Halloween show.

33:22.768 --> 33:24.701
I never perform

33:24.703 --> 33:26.103
On Halloween.
You're contractually

33:26.105 --> 33:28.372
Obligated to do
three specials a year.
I said

33:28.374 --> 33:32.109
I will not perform on Halloween.

33:32.111 --> 33:33.777
Darling, they've booked
andy williams.

33:33.779 --> 33:35.278
Imagine you two singing

33:35.280 --> 33:38.281
"autumn leaves"
in matching pumpkin suits--

33:38.283 --> 33:40.283
America will
lap it up.

33:40.285 --> 33:42.119
(short laugh)

33:42.121 --> 33:45.789
You know, when I first met him,

33:45.791 --> 33:49.292
He was some
junior so-and-so,

33:49.294 --> 33:51.962
Hanging out in the
lobby of the studio.

33:51.964 --> 33:54.898
I made him my manager.

33:54.900 --> 33:57.734
And then...

33:57.736 --> 33:59.236
I made the colossal mistake

33:59.238 --> 34:01.238
Of marrying him.

34:01.240 --> 34:03.573
And now he thinks he
knows better than I

34:03.575 --> 34:05.809
What my audience wants.

34:10.148 --> 34:11.648
I live to serve.

34:11.650 --> 34:15.585
There will be no Halloween show.

34:15.587 --> 34:17.521
You got that, chickies?

34:17.523 --> 34:19.489
Where are
you going?

34:23.327 --> 34:26.263
I have a luncheon engagement...

34:26.265 --> 34:28.331
At home.

34:32.937 --> 34:35.005
<i>(door closes)</i>

34:48.619 --> 34:52.689
Tell me-- what have you
been doing since florida?

34:52.691 --> 34:56.460
I'm sorry that I had to run
off the way I did, but...

34:56.462 --> 34:58.295
You know my motto:

34:58.297 --> 35:00.797
Always leave them wanting more.

35:00.799 --> 35:03.633
I left when you left.

35:03.635 --> 35:05.035
Please, let's sit.

35:05.037 --> 35:07.971
I went to,
uh, nevada.
Nevada?

35:07.973 --> 35:10.640
Ah.
Thank you.

35:10.642 --> 35:12.642
Uh, the army, uh,

35:12.644 --> 35:16.246
They wanted carpenters,
uh, that they could, uh,

35:16.248 --> 35:18.315
Use to build villages, uh,

35:18.317 --> 35:20.484
To blow up
with their atomic bombs.

35:20.486 --> 35:24.154
It took us ages
to build these towns

35:24.156 --> 35:26.823
And then-- boom!
Gone. In a flash.

35:26.825 --> 35:28.825
(speaks italian)
(short chuckle)

35:28.827 --> 35:31.628
Yes, I know what that's like.

35:32.997 --> 35:35.398
Elsa.
Hmm?

35:35.400 --> 35:38.235
I have seen your star ascend.

35:41.339 --> 35:42.739
(grunts)

35:42.741 --> 35:44.341
Massimo:
<i>If I would have told you,</i>

35:44.343 --> 35:46.476
<i>As you lay</i>
<i>in my workshop in berlin...</i>

35:48.079 --> 35:49.579
<i>...That all this</i>
<i>was soon to come,</i>

35:49.581 --> 35:50.914
<i>You would have said</i>

35:50.916 --> 35:53.083
That I was mad.
Now look at you.

35:53.085 --> 35:55.819
You have everything
you ever wanted. Huh?

35:57.755 --> 36:00.023
I'm bored.

36:00.025 --> 36:02.092
And I am alone.

36:04.362 --> 36:07.531
All my friends are
on the payroll.

36:07.533 --> 36:09.533
They say yes to
anything I ask

36:09.535 --> 36:11.201
Because they know
if they don't,

36:11.203 --> 36:14.204
They will be cast out
of the paradise known as

36:14.206 --> 36:16.940
<i>The elsa mars hour.</i>

36:22.613 --> 36:25.115
My husband cheats on me.

36:25.117 --> 36:27.350
I cheat on him.

36:30.288 --> 36:31.788
No, massimo,

36:31.790 --> 36:33.290
I have always, always,

36:33.292 --> 36:35.792
Always been cursed.

36:35.794 --> 36:38.628
First by...

36:38.630 --> 36:40.897
Having my dreams
ripped away.

36:40.899 --> 36:43.567
And now I am cursed by
having them all come true.

36:43.569 --> 36:46.570
Oh, you are tired,
uh, exhausted.

36:46.572 --> 36:48.071
That is all.

36:48.073 --> 36:50.140
Eight years ago...

36:53.477 --> 36:55.579
...My best friend

36:55.581 --> 36:57.814
Made me a birthday cake.

36:57.816 --> 37:00.417
That night,

37:00.419 --> 37:02.819
When she and
I sat over

37:02.821 --> 37:05.589
My candle, my birthday wish

37:05.591 --> 37:09.326
Was plain and simple.

37:09.328 --> 37:12.062
I just wanted to be loved.

37:14.332 --> 37:16.333
Little did I know that

37:16.335 --> 37:18.501
Every step that I
would take since then

37:18.503 --> 37:21.171
Would be one step
further away from

37:21.173 --> 37:23.573
Making that wish...

37:23.575 --> 37:25.642
Come true.

37:28.179 --> 37:29.613
Let's run away together.

37:29.615 --> 37:31.114
Yes.
Like we talked about
in the old days.

37:31.116 --> 37:32.449
Do you remember?

37:32.451 --> 37:34.951
We could find an
apartment in rome

37:34.953 --> 37:36.953
On the appian way.
(chuckling)

37:36.955 --> 37:38.788
Refresh my italian, no?

37:38.790 --> 37:42.525
Get good and fat,
grow old together.

37:44.528 --> 37:46.529
Please.

37:46.531 --> 37:48.598
I just...

37:50.301 --> 37:52.469
I need to be with
someone I love.

37:52.471 --> 37:56.373
Um, elsa,
now I am cursed...

37:56.375 --> 37:57.974
With a dream
that comes too late.

37:57.976 --> 38:00.143
I came to...

38:00.145 --> 38:03.213
To say good-bye.

38:03.215 --> 38:04.714
I, uh...

38:04.716 --> 38:07.484
I have

38:07.486 --> 38:09.486
A disease in my lungs, uh,

38:09.488 --> 38:11.488
That has gone into my bones.

38:11.490 --> 38:14.491
Uh, they say
that I only have a month.

38:14.493 --> 38:16.159
(exclaims)

38:16.161 --> 38:19.396
And then I will be gone.

38:26.170 --> 38:28.738
And now there will be
no one left, huh?

38:32.843 --> 38:34.911
Well.

38:34.913 --> 38:36.680
(sniffles)

38:40.584 --> 38:42.585
(door opens)
michael: Elsa?

38:42.587 --> 38:44.254
(door closes)

38:44.256 --> 38:47.190
Leave me alone,
michael, I'm drinking.

38:47.192 --> 38:49.259
Hello, elsa.

38:53.264 --> 38:55.999
(short chuckle)

38:57.535 --> 39:01.204
You should have called, huh?

39:01.206 --> 39:04.040
I did not know you were bringing
mr. Gable home with you.

39:04.042 --> 39:05.875
I do hope

39:05.877 --> 39:07.444
The head of the network

39:07.446 --> 39:10.447
Didn't come all the way out here

39:10.449 --> 39:14.451
To talk to me about
the Halloween show, because...

39:14.453 --> 39:16.286
I've made up my mind

39:16.288 --> 39:18.788
And I am not going to do it.

39:18.790 --> 39:20.623
This isn't about
Halloween, elsa.

39:20.625 --> 39:22.192
No?

39:23.794 --> 39:25.028
(giggles)

39:26.230 --> 39:27.964
This sounds serious.

39:30.234 --> 39:32.068
Can I get you
a drink, mr. Gable?

39:32.070 --> 39:34.471
Could definitely
use one.

39:38.909 --> 39:42.979
Now, why don't you tell me
what this is all about?

39:44.982 --> 39:47.584
It seems hedda hopper
got her hands

39:47.586 --> 39:51.254
On some eight millimeter films
you shot back in germany.

39:51.256 --> 39:53.256
The content--

39:53.258 --> 39:54.591
How can I put this?--

39:54.593 --> 39:56.659
Is quite graphic in nature.

39:59.597 --> 40:02.599
I don't know.

40:02.601 --> 40:05.268
Fakes, forgeries?

40:05.270 --> 40:07.103
It's not me.

40:07.105 --> 40:08.772
It looked a lot like you, elsa.

40:08.774 --> 40:11.241
You've seen them?
Gable:
Just now.

40:11.243 --> 40:13.276
Mr. Chandler over at the <i>times</i>
<i>is a close personal friend.</i>

40:13.278 --> 40:16.613
He gave us
a private screening.

40:16.615 --> 40:18.615
No one's gonna believe
it's not you.

40:18.617 --> 40:21.518
You told me you lost
your legs in a rail accident.

40:21.520 --> 40:23.520
You lied to me?

40:23.522 --> 40:25.522
That's what we do.

40:25.524 --> 40:27.791
We lie to each other.

40:27.793 --> 40:29.959
This whole marriage

40:29.961 --> 40:33.129
Is one stinking, stupid,

40:33.131 --> 40:34.464
Ugly lie!

40:34.466 --> 40:37.267
I'll pack my things.

40:40.304 --> 40:41.805
Mr. Gable,

40:41.807 --> 40:43.206
We can fix this, right?

40:43.208 --> 40:44.641
I mean...

40:44.643 --> 40:46.643
I mean, everybody
has a price, right?

40:46.645 --> 40:48.711
We tried to reason
with miss hopper,

40:48.713 --> 40:49.813
She won't have it.

40:49.815 --> 40:52.816
She's publishing
her article next week.

40:52.818 --> 40:54.384
But that will ruin me.

41:01.325 --> 41:04.494
I'll become...
(chuckles lightly)

41:04.496 --> 41:07.997
Just some...

41:07.999 --> 41:10.667
Bizarre footnote
in hollywood history.

41:10.669 --> 41:13.236
There's one more thing.

41:13.238 --> 41:15.004
What?

41:15.006 --> 41:17.440
Hopper hired some amateur
sleuth to retrace your steps.

41:17.442 --> 41:20.844
Which led back to
jupiter, florida.

41:20.846 --> 41:23.246
Apparently, you ran
a freak show.

41:23.248 --> 41:25.081
Yes.

41:25.083 --> 41:26.449
For a short time.

41:26.451 --> 41:28.084
It was an act of charity.

41:28.086 --> 41:30.086
I just, uh...

41:30.088 --> 41:32.021
I felt sorry for them.

41:32.023 --> 41:34.090
Sorry?
(laughs)

41:37.027 --> 41:38.261
They're all dead.

41:42.032 --> 41:44.100
What?

41:46.036 --> 41:48.037
All of them?

41:48.039 --> 41:51.040
There was some kind of massacre.

41:51.042 --> 41:53.042
Bodies found in a mass grave.

41:53.044 --> 41:56.613
I don't know if you read the
fine print in your contract,

41:56.615 --> 41:58.681
But there's a
morals clause.

42:00.117 --> 42:02.185
Obviously, we'll pay
out your contract.

42:06.123 --> 42:07.524
I've changed my mind.

42:09.460 --> 42:11.528
About what?

42:13.898 --> 42:18.034
I will perform on Halloween.

42:20.571 --> 42:22.572
Why not?

42:22.574 --> 42:23.907
(chuckles)

42:23.909 --> 42:26.309
Might as well go out
with a bang.

42:41.425 --> 42:42.825
Places, everyone.

42:42.827 --> 42:46.329
Elsa mars'
Halloween spooktacular.

42:50.834 --> 42:53.770
And we are on
in five, four,

42:53.772 --> 42:55.772
Three, two...

42:55.774 --> 42:57.840
(applause)

43:05.282 --> 43:08.351
(david bowie's "heroes" begins)

43:22.132 --> 43:25.468
â™ª I...

43:25.470 --> 43:27.870
â™ª I wish you could swim

43:30.474 --> 43:33.810
â™ª like the dolphins

43:33.812 --> 43:36.546
â™ª like dolphins can swim

43:39.483 --> 43:41.484
â™ª though nothing

43:41.486 --> 43:44.554
â™ª nothing will keep us
together â™ª

43:47.324 --> 43:50.994
â™ª we can beat them

43:50.996 --> 43:55.398
â™ª forever and ever

43:55.400 --> 43:59.669
â™ª oh, we can be heroes

43:59.671 --> 44:01.838
â™ª just for one day

44:01.840 --> 44:04.841
Desiree: Boys, hold on
to your daddy's hand.

44:04.843 --> 44:06.175
Hey, hey, come
back here.

44:06.177 --> 44:07.844
Give me your hand.

44:07.846 --> 44:09.579
